    <p>The Hosmer–Lemeshow Chi-square goodness of fit test showed a (χ<xref rid="R2" ref-type="bibr">2</xref>) value of 13.49 and corresponding significance of 0.03, thus revealing a poor calibration of the model. The AUC of ROC was 0.698 with confidence interval of 0.50-0.88 indicating a fair but not good discrimination ability of the model [<xref rid="ija_24_22-f002" ref-type="fig">Figure 2</xref>].</p>
